---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How We Review" description="Our methodology for researching, rating, and ranking products on HonestPickReview.">
  <div class="container" style="padding-top: 24px;">
    <p class="breadcrumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> / How We Review</p>
  </div>
  <article class="container prose" style="max-width: 720px; padding-bottom: 48px;">
    <h1>How We Review Products</h1>
    <p>
      Every review published on HonestPickReview follows the same research process, so ratings stay
      consistent and comparable across categories.
    </p>
    <h2>1. Specification Research</h2>
    <p>
      We start by collecting manufacturer specifications, materials, dimensions, and stated performance
      claims directly from official product documentation.
    </p>
    <h2>2. Buyer Feedback Analysis</h2>
    <p>
      We look for consistent patterns across verified buyer feedback — recurring praise or complaints —
      rather than relying on any single review, positive or negative.
    </p>
    <h2>3. Category Comparison</h2>
    <p>
      Each product is benchmarked against similar alternatives in its category on price, feature set, and
      build quality to judge whether it's genuinely competitive.
    </p>
    <h2>4. Rating Scale</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>4.5–5.0:</strong> Excellent — few meaningful drawbacks for its price and category.</li>
      <li><strong>4.0–4.4:</strong> Very good — solid choice with minor trade-offs.</li>
      <li><strong>3.5–3.9:</strong> Good — usable but with notable limitations worth knowing about.</li>
      <li><strong>Below 3.5:</strong> We generally don't publish standalone reviews for these; they may appear only in comparison context.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>5. Ongoing Updates</h2>
    <p>
      Reviews are revisited periodically to reflect price changes, new buyer feedback, or newer competing
      products. The "last updated" date on each review reflects the most recent check.
    </p>
    <p>
      Read our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a> to understand how we're compensated
      and why it doesn't affect our ratings.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
